<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5b6045fb-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c" identifier="/us/usc/t29/s2106"><num value="2106">§ 2106.</num><heading> Procedures encouraged where not required</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">It is the sense of Congress that an employer who is not required to comply with the notice requirements of <ref href="/us/usc/t29/s2102">section 2102 of this title</ref> should, to the extent possible, provide notice to its employees about a proposal to close a plant or permanently reduce its workforce.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5b6045fc-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/379/s7">Pub. L. 100–379, § 7</ref>, <date date="1988-08-04">Aug. 4, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/894">102 Stat. 894</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id5b6045fd-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id5b6045fe-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id5b6045ff-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective 6 months after <date date="1988-08-04">Aug. 4, 1988</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/100/379/s11">section 11 of Pub. L. 100–379</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t29/s2101">section 2101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
